task.summary: Added classes related to the Model. I'm trying to figure out how to create @OneToMany relationship with a super abstract class (this would be done in order to have one single @OneToMany relationship from Station to Datum, instead of having four different @OneToMany from Station to DatumCountry, from Station to DatumCity...).
Solved issue related to the previous commit. First version of the working model.
I am having troubles in linking the stylesheet.css to the homepage. I will fix it ASAP.
Added a sidemenu bar with export data and import data options (not implemented yet). The side menu bar is still not responsive.

The sidemenu has been deleted. The upload data feature has pending changes: if the station to which new data belong doesn't exist yet a new station must be created, it is necessary to handle also this case. Moreover I am trying to find a better solution to display the existing stations in the popup.
Now it is possible to update new data of ALREADY EXISTENT stations (with type coherent with .csv header). Some other stuff (listed in TODOs) must be managed.
Code related to the uploadDataModal has been cleaned up.
Front-end part for create station has been completed. Some code clean-up has been done.
